---
title: HiTicket - Sequence Diagram - Chatbot Ticket Creation
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Chatbot as Chatbot UI
    participant API as Express API
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant TicketModel as Ticket Model
    participant Gmail as Gmail API

    User->>Chatbot: Navigate to /chatbot
    Chatbot-->>User: Step 1 - Display 10 category tiles
    User->>Chatbot: Select category
    Chatbot-->>User: Step 2 - Display sub-type chips for that category
    User->>Chatbot: Select sub-type
    Chatbot-->>User: Step 3 - Description input with KB deflection

    Chatbot->>API: GET /api/kb?q=description keywords (JWT not required)
    API->>DB: KbArticle.find({ $text: { $search: query }, isPublished: true })
    DB-->>API: matching KB articles
    API-->>Chatbot: KB articles array
    Chatbot-->>User: Show KB suggestion chips - resolve without ticket?
    User->>Chatbot: Dismiss KB suggestions - proceed to raise ticket

    note over Chatbot: keyword regex auto-detects priority (critical/urgent/down)
    Chatbot-->>User: Step 4 - Confirmation summary screen
    User->>Chatbot: Confirm and submit

    Chatbot->>API: POST /api/tickets { title, description, category, subType, priority } + JWT
    note over API: protect middleware - verify JWT, tokenVersion, reject 2fa-pending tokens
    API->>DB: getNextAgent() - count open tickets per active agent
    DB-->>API: least-loaded agent name (round-robin)

    loop Up to 3 attempts on duplicate ticketId collision
        API->>TicketModel: Ticket.create({ fields, createdBy, assignedTo: agent.name })
        TicketModel->>TicketModel: pre save - find last TKT-NNNN, increment, assign ticketId
        TicketModel->>TicketModel: pre save - push HistoryEntry (Ticket created, by System)
        TicketModel->>DB: INSERT ticket document
        DB-->>TicketModel: saved ticket or 11000 duplicate key on ticketId
    end

    API->>DB: ticket.populate(createdBy name email)
    DB-->>API: populated ticket
    API-->>Chatbot: 201 { ticket }
    Chatbot-->>User: Navigate to /tickets/:id

    API--)Gmail: sendTicketCreated(ticket, user) async fire-and-forget
